# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Line-ending policy
#
# Goal: keep line endings deterministic regardless of each contributor's
# `core.autocrlf` setting, so diffs don't show spurious LF<->CRLF changes.
#
# How it works:
#   * In the repository, text files are stored normalized to LF.
#   * On checkout, the working-tree ending is decided by the rules below.
#   * Windows-native scripts (.ps1/.bat/.cmd) are checked out as CRLF because
#     they are run by Windows tooling that expects CRLF.
#   * Unix scripts (.sh) are forced to LF so they stay executable on Linux/macOS.
#
# See LINE-ENDINGS.md for the rationale and the one-time renormalize command.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Default: let Git detect text vs binary and normalize text to LF in the repo.
* text=auto

# Windows-native scripts — check out as CRLF.
*.ps1   text eol=crlf
*.bat   text eol=crlf
*.cmd   text eol=crlf

# Unix shell scripts — must stay LF.
*.sh    text eol=lf

# Explicit binary files — never normalize or diff as text.
*.ico   binary
*.db    binary
